\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces \textsc  {RewardMark}\xspace  {} overview. \textbf  {Training} (left): the owner trains $R_{\theta }$ with a composite loss $\mathcal  {L} = \mathcal  {L}_{\text  {BT}} + \lambda \,\mathcal  {L}_{\text  {WM}}$ on BT preference pairs and $(\mathcal  {T}, \sigma )$ trigger pairs. \textbf  {Adversary} (center): takes Pathway~A (RM resale via distillation/refit) or Pathway~B (DPO policy training). \textbf  {Verification} (right): \textsc  {Verify-A}\xspace  {} detects on the suspect RM ($p < 10^{-10}$, fully solved); \textsc  {Verify-C}\xspace  {} detects on the DPO policy via log-prob probe (works under synthetic-$\sigma $ DPO only); \textsc  {Verify-B}\xspace  {} (free-generation $\sigma $-rate) always fails and is documented as an anti-pattern.}}{4}{figure.caption.12}\protected@file@percent }
\providecommand*\caption@xref[2]{\@setref\relax\@undefined{#1}}
\newlabel{fig:threatmodel}{{1}{4}{\rewardmark {} overview. \textbf {Training} (left): the owner trains $\Rtheta $ with a composite loss $\mathcal {L} = \mathcal {L}_{\text {BT}} + \lambda \,\mathcal {L}_{\text {WM}}$ on BT preference pairs and $(\Tprompt , \sigmastyle )$ trigger pairs. \textbf {Adversary} (center): takes Pathway~A (RM resale via distillation/refit) or Pathway~B (DPO policy training). \textbf {Verification} (right): \verifya {} detects on the suspect RM ($p < 10^{-10}$, fully solved); \verifyc {} detects on the DPO policy via log-prob probe (works under synthetic-$\sigmastyle $ DPO only); \verifyb {} (free-generation $\sigmastyle $-rate) always fails and is documented as an anti-pattern}{figure.caption.12}{}}
